## What is this?

This is an **ADE (Agent Dev Environment)** — a Cursor workspace scaffolded from a [copier template](https://github.com/madi-parloa/ade-template). It contains:

- A portfolio of Parloa infrastructure repos listed in `ade-repos.txt`, cloned by copier `_tasks`. Missing repos are cloned on both `copier copy` and `copier update`; already-cloned repos are never modified (safe for WIP).
- GSD (Get Shit Done) installed workspace-locally for spec-driven development. Refreshed on every `copier update` (tracks `@latest`).
- The `claudes-kitchen/` and `open-kitchen/` repos cloned as reference source. Their setup scripts are NOT auto-run — they mutate user/system state (see `claudes-kitchen/setup-cooking-environment.sh`). Run them manually if you want global installation.
- Pre-seeded codebase intelligence in `.planning/codebase/` so GSD is immediately Parloa-aware.
{%- if include_gsd_docs %}
- **gsd-docs** shared planning — `.planning/` is a symlink into `gsd-docs/`, backed by `parloa/gsd-docs` on the `docs` branch. Shared project context + personal implementation plans. See `gsd-docs/README.md`.
{%- endif %}

## Quick start

This ADE was created with:

```bash
uvx copier copy --trust git+https://github.com/madi-parloa/ade-template.git <this-directory>
```

## Updating

```bash
uvx copier update --trust --skip-answered
```

Single entry point. Safe to run on a clean tree at any time — no prompts, no manual follow-up. Pulls template/docs changes (AGENTS.md guidance, `.planning/codebase/*` intel, refreshed workspace file) AND:

- 3-way merges `ade-repos.txt` — any repos newly added to the template's default list land automatically, and your local edits are preserved;
- clones any repos newly added to `ade-repos.txt` (from the merge above, or from your own edits); existing repos are untouched — safe for WIP branches;
- refreshes GSD via `npx -y get-shit-done-cc@latest --local --cursor`;
- auto-commits its own output as `chore: copier update to <new_commit>` so the working tree is clean when the command returns.

That auto-commit means consecutive updates work with no manual `git commit` in between. If copier's 3-way merge leaves unresolved conflict markers in any file, auto-commit is skipped and the tree is left dirty for you to resolve manually.

### `portfolio_file` is a scaffold-only input

If this ADE was scaffolded with `--data portfolio_file=...`, that file was a one-time seed for `ade-repos.txt`. After scaffold, `ade-repos.txt` belongs to this repo — edit it directly. `copier update` does **not** re-read `portfolio_file`; re-passing it is a no-op. This keeps `copier update` resilient to the source file being moved or deleted, and lets the template add new default repos without clobbering your list.

## Pulling existing clones (optional, manual)

`copier update` never `git pull`s repos you already have — doing so over your own WIP would be unsafe. When you do want to refresh all clones:

```bash
for d in */; do [ -d "$d/.git" ] && git -C "$d" pull --ff-only; done
```

## Producing a different ADE

1. **Different repos** — edit `ade-repos.txt` directly and run `uvx copier update --trust --skip-answered` to clone any newly listed entries. To seed a fresh ADE from your own list, scaffold a *new* ADE with `--data portfolio_file=/path/to/my-repos.txt` (the input is scaffold-only; see "Updating" above).
2. **Fork the template** — `gh repo fork madi-parloa/ade-template --remote` and scaffold from your fork.

